#ad I want to encourage you guys to participate in Plastic Free July by committing to wearing and recycling denim made from cotton—a natural fiber that breaks down relatively quickly and does not shed microplastics when washed (that then can end up in the ocean)*👖🏔️🌿

@discovercotton’s Blue Jeans Go Green™ program is here to help—both with physically recycling your denim and with better understanding the denim recycling process. 

Cotton’s @BlueJeansGoGreen program helps collect and recycle authentic denim. Since it’s made from cotton, a natural fiber, it can be broken down to its original state and transformed in creative ways. 

Just drop off your old denim at a local participating retailer and you might even get a discount on new denim just for recycling! Find out more at the BlueJeansGoGreen.org

**New Study Press Release - CottonToday (cottoninc.com) https://bit.ly/3JK7PGM
